2, Greek Sources.

All Cicero's philosophical and rhetorical writings were con- fessedly founded more or less on Greek originals.⁶ The stores from which he principally drew in writing the Cato Maior are clearly indicated, in several parts of the work. Passages from Xenophon’s Oeconomicus are translated in Chapters 17 and 22.
